%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 512a72de08c75cf4e8a8424f7b75a271, type: 3}
  m_Name: D1T15_AdvisorTalkAfterPillJob
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  npc: 0
  sequence:
  - dialogueText: You handled that box well. Most would've fumbled it in the dark.
    buttonText: I'm efficient
  - dialogueText: Good. You've earned my trust with that box. It's about more than
      just deliveries.
    buttonText: Your trust?
  - dialogueText: More than you know. Now, you need to see this island for what it
      really is.
    buttonText: Explain
  - dialogueText: Take one. These pills... they peel back the night. They let you
      see the strings.
    buttonText: No thanks
  - dialogueText: Don't be a fool. Knowledge is the only weapon you've got in this
      shithole.
    buttonText: I refuse
  - dialogueText: Still playing it safe? You trust my tasks, but you don't trust
      me.
    buttonText: Exactly
  - dialogueText: Heh. Fair enough. In this bar, paranoia is a survival skill. Let
      me prove my worth.
    buttonText: How?
  - dialogueText: Look up. See that loony pacing on the balcony? The one talking
      to the stars.
    buttonText: I see him
  - dialogueText: My gut says he's got a piece of the puzzle. A secret the Boss forgot
      to bury.
    buttonText: A puzzle?
  - dialogueText: Go. Talk to him. If he babbles nonsense, I'm a liar. If not...
      we talk again.
    buttonText: I'm going
  - dialogueText: Don't take too long. Truth has a habit of disappearing when the
      sun rises.
    buttonText: Understood
